S3 buckets and objects:
  Amazon S3 stores data as objects within buckets.
  An object includes a file and any metadata that describes the file.
  You can control access to the bucket and its objects.
  Bucket policies:
    Resource-based policy for an S3 bucket.
    Effect, Action and Resource are mandatory.
  Access Points:
    unique DNS and ARN name
    disinct permissions and network controls
  Encryption:
    - SSE-S3 managed
    - SSE-KMS managed
    - Dual-layer SSE
    - Customized encryption
S3 storage classes:
  Express One Zone
  Standard
  Standard-IA
  Glacier Instant retrieval
  Glacier Flexible retrieval
  Glacier Deep archive
  Intelligient-tiering - Automatic tiering of objects to storage class based on access pattern.
Lifecycle policies:
  Transition objects to another storage class in an automated way.
  Object expiry or deletion can also be handled.
  Ex: Move objects older than 30days to S3 Standarad-IA
      Move objects older thna 365 days to Glacier Deep Archive.
